Large Lot, over 1/3 Acre within the controlled subdivision of Ocean View Estates. Lot is located in a quiet cul-de-sac complete with curbs and sidewalks. Beautiful Residential building lot tucked away in the Samish Neighborhood. The property is located at the northeast corner of the intersection of Dumas Avenue and Ashley Street, both full width rights of way; there is an undeveloped plated alley right of way to the east of the property. The property is covered in grasses, native vegetation and trees. There is an existing garage located off the alley access to the east. There are no identified critical areas (wetlands, streams, habitat areas or steep slopes) on the property Water, gas and electricity are in the street. The main sewer line is close by on Ashley St and development of the lot would require connection. Easy access to I-5, downtown and everything Bellingham has to offer.

text: Tri-Level home with a great floor plan, nice flow and vaulted ceilings. Covered front porch offers views of the forest. The house sits in the middle of a double lot, so there is plenty of neighbor separation. All the rooms are large. Downstairs room is the biggest and could easily be a rec room. Primary bedroom has ensuite with 2 sinks and walk-in closet. Back patio off of the kitchen offers private place to enjoy the property. Large garage an long driveway for plenty of parking. enormous amount of dry storage area under the home.

Help! I was a great looking home when I was built in '62 but unfortunately I was left all alone a few years back & I haven't been the same since. I'm perched on a pretty good sized lot & within walking distance to amazing Maple Beach. At my heart is a cozy fireplace to gather around & I provide 2 bedrooms & a full bathroom. I even have a new skylight that wasn't exactly planned but you can now stargaze through the roof! I'm a bit saggy on the right hand side. Looking for a long term relationship with a new owner to bring me back to my good old self or better! I'm gonna be a lot of work but hopefully a rewarding experience. Call my great broker to discuss. PS... I'm offered up at way below assessed value to make me more interesting!
